critical_positive: I think our personalities were pretty compatible for this conversation. My partner was very chatty and willing to share her views, while I was quite willing to listen. She had some pretty amusing and interesting things to say. Also, neither of us seemed particularly shy so I think that contributed greatly to the flow of our conversation.
critical_negative: I think the only thing that didn't work well was that my partner couldn't really find out much about me. Though I listed it as a positive, my partner loved talking about herself, which isn't necessarily a bad thing. However, this did result in me not finding many openings to talk about myself.
